flowRoot.flowPara: Apolipoprotein E (APOE) is found in the chylomicron and Intermediate-density lipoprotein (IDLs) is the principal cholesterol carrier in the brain, mainly produced by astrocytes. Its gene is mapped to chromosome 19 in a cluster with APOC1 and APOC2 and is polymorphic with three major alleles E2, E3 and E4. The E4 isoform is involved in Alzheimerâ€™s and cardiovascular disease with evidence suggesting an interaction with amyloid. In addition, there is also evidence of possible increased episodic memory ability and neural efficiency in younger E4 carriers.
